Basic Linux Commands Cheat Sheet

: File & Directory Management
ls : List files and directories in the current location.
ls -l : List files/directories with detailed information (permissions, size, owner, etc.).
pwd : Show the current working directory (your location).
mkdir <directory_name> : Create a new directory.
rmdir <directory_name> : Remove an empty directory.
rm -r <directory_name> : Remove a directory and its contents recursively.
cd <directory_name> : Change to the specified directory.
cd .. : Move one level up (exit current directory).

: File Operations
touch <file_name> : Create a new empty file.
cat <file_name> : Display the content of a file.
zcat <file_name> : View the content of a compressed .gz file.
head <file_name> : Display the first 10 lines of a file (use -n to specify lines).
tail <file_name> : Display the last 10 lines of a file (use -n to specify lines).
tail -f <file_name> : Continuously monitor a file for new updates.
less <file_name> : View a file page by page with navigation.
more <file_name> : View a file page by page (limited navigation).

: File Editing & Writing
echo "message" > <file_name> : Write message to a file (overwrites if file exists).
echo "message" >> <file_name> : Append message to a file.
vi <file_name> : Open the file in the vi editor to edit or insert text.
tee <file_name> : Write input to a file and display it on the screen.

: File & Directory Copy/Move
cp <file_name> <destination_folder>/ : Copy a file to a specified folder.
cp -r <directory_name> <destination_folder>/ : Copy a directory and its contents to a destination.
mv <file_name> <destination_folder>/ : Move a file to another folder (can also rename).

: File & Text Processing
wc <file_name> : Count lines, words, and characters in a file.
diff <file1> <file2> : Show differences between two files.
sort <file_name> : Sort the contents of a file alphabetically.
cut -b <range> <file_name> : Extract specific byte(s) from each line of a file.

: Links
ln -s <target_path> <link_name> : Create a symbolic (soft) link to a file or directory.

: Miscellaneous
clear : Clear the terminal screen.


